1. Home, dear home, we never can forget,

OUR OWN DEAR HOME.
4

2. Lured by gain we seek a foreign shore, Worn and weary keep the golden ore; Still our yearning hearts demand Rest in the homestead in our native land.
3. On the gilded page of earthly fame Some may pant to register their name; Round our names no wreath may be,
But you may read them on the old home tree.
